Workers at the troubled Mafube Municipality in the Free State who’ve not been paid salaries for two months are now calling on the national government’s intervention. eNCA’s Moloko Moloto is in the Free State with more. Courtesy of #DStv403Show less  JOHANNESBURG - He’s blind and has had his leg amputated. But despite these challenges, a Free State man still hasn’t received his pension payout, five years since he stopped working for Mafube Local Municipality. That's because the municipality hasn’t been paying worker’s contributions to the pension fund scheme. READ: Why South Africa’s new pension rules are good for investors: economist Many other former employees of Mafube Municipality face a similar dilemma and those who still work and haven’t received salaries for two months now. * eNCA’s Moloko Moloto reports.